South Africa’s Solidarity Labor Union Declares Dispute With Eskom on Wages

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-08-30T12:17:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/south-africa-s-solidarity-labor-union-declares-dispute-with-eskom-on-wages.html
South Africa ’s Solidarity labor
union has declared a dispute with Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd., the
country’s state-owned power company, over a unilateral decision
to increase wages by 7 percent.  Solidarity, based in Johannesburg, commented in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
